Image Steganography Web App using Flask
This project allows you to securely hide secret messages inside images and retrieve them later using Least Significant Bit (LSB) steganography. Built with Flask and Pillow, this web application provides a simple interface to encode and decode messages in images.

🚀 Features

Hide secret text messages inside PNG images.

Extract hidden messages from encoded images.

Simple web interface using Flask.

Supports image download after encoding.

Optional: Add encryption using cryptography (expandable).

🛠️ Tech Stack

Python

Flask (Web Framework)

Pillow (Image Processing)

HTML, CSS (Templates)

Optional: cryptography (For message encryption)

📂 Complete Project Structure:
image_steganography_flask/
├── app.py
├── stegano.py
├── requirements.txt
├── templates/
│ ├── index.html
│ └── result.html
├── static/
│ ├── css/
│ │ └── style.css
│ └── images/
└── README.md

📦 Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone <repository_link>
cd image_steganography_flask

Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt

If Pillow or cryptography are missing:
pip install Pillow cryptography

Run the Flask app:
python app.py

Open your browser:
http://127.0.0.1:5000